},{"number":2,"category":"family","header":"Two marriages; four children with Levi Hare","body":"Coris Ann's first marriage to Levi Hare (born May 26, 1837 New York) produced four documented children. After Levi's death she married William Hodges without further documented children. The two-marriage household was typical of nineteenth-century American widows who remarried for economic and social support; her second marriage placed her in the sorghum-molasses trade economy of Walworth County Wisconsin."},{"number":3,"category":"family","header":"Moriah NY 1843 to Elkhorn Wisconsin 1927","body":"Coris Ann Bartlett was born July 21, 1843 in Moriah, Essex County New York — during her father Truman Bartlett's New York years before the family's 1844 migration to Wisconsin. She died April 6, 1927 in Elkhorn, Walworth County Wisconsin at age eighty-three. She is buried at Mount Pleasant Cemetery, Tibbets Wisconsin alongside her parents — a three-generation Wisconsin family cemetery cluster."}],"cross_connections":[],"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"coris-hodges-1843"}},"burialCemetery":null,"institutionsById":{},"crossConnections":[]}